    <note>Luo(1) Shaowei [7047] He was a Later Liang official. Yanji's [1264] grandfather. According to Han(1) Guohua's [651] funerary inscription, Yanji was his wife's father and Shaowei his wife's grandfather. However, a funerary inscription for Luo(1) Zhoujing [3607] in QTW lists Shaowei as his father, Hongxin [3608] as his great grandfather and Zhoujing's sons as Yanshang [3610], Yanxu [3609] and Yanzong [3611]. This would make Shaowei Han(1) Guohua's [651] great grandfather-in-law. Shaowei's wife was the third daughter of the Yanzhou jiedu shi, Liu(2). Zhoujing died in 937 at the age of 33. He served as a military official under the Later Tang and Later Jin. His second wife was the fifth daughter of the Dongchuan jiedu shi, Xu(3). QTW, 852.3a-8a; Renming da cidian. 《唐代人物知識ベース》記其生卒年為：877 - 910.</note>
